of
the
world
as
appears
at
first;
for
a
very
narrow
income
has
a
tendency
to
contract
the
mind,
and
sour
the
temper.
Those
who
can
barely
live,
and
who
live
perforce
in
a
very
small,
and
generally
very
inferior,
society,
may
well
be
illiberal
and
cross.
This
does
not
apply,
however,
to
Miss
Bates;
she
is
only
too
good
